		<p class="pagename">New York Region</p>
<p class="text">CWC schools are located in communities where parents are demanding challenging and joyful learning environments that serve diverse communities. As of the 2015-16 school year, CWC has two schools in New York serving some 500 children. <a href="../../files/Chad_Ferguson.pdf" target="_blank">Meet</a> Chad Ferguson, Executive Director of CWC New York.</p>
<p class="text"><a href="http://www.cwc-newyork.org/" target="_blank">CWC New York Website</a></p>
<p class="text"><a href="http://www.cwc-williamsburg.org/" target="_blank">CWC Williamsburg opened in 2013</a></p>
<p class="text"><a href="http://www.cwc-crownheights.org/pd/cwcch/index.html" target="_blank">CWC Crown Heights opened in 2013</a></p>
<p class="text">Our New York schools are in strong demand:  In 2015, we had over 600 applications for both schools, including approximately 450 applications for 130 kindergarten seats. The 2015-16 school year will be the first in which CWC New York’s schools participate in statewide assessments.  </p>
<p class="text">For more information on CWC New York, including how to enroll in the schools, please visit their <a href="http://www.cwc-newyork.org/pd/CWCNY/index.html" target="_blank">website</a>.</p>	</div>
